lines.text: waiting at the door
in the garden of delight
next day's almost gone,
mem'ries glance inside
listen to a voice we know so well
the voice of faith
the voice that came one day
that day when we knew where we had to go
see silent thunder echo by
we'll never come back from this flight
we're longing for a new escape
don't wake me up don't wake me up
don't wake me up
swinging through the air on a golden leaf
from above the twinkling eye is watching me
only me and you but where have all the hope
and glory gone, for long all gone
do you know where they all have gone
see silent thunder echo by
we'll never come back from this flight
we're longing for a new escape
don't wake me up don't wake me up
don't wake me up
don't wake me up
don't wake me up
don't wake me up
it seems that we shall realize the truth
nothing changed except the colour of the blue
let him wander through the land of morning dew
where he shall find the truth
hush hush hush hush
don't make him think about his best mistakes

don't wake me up

don't wake me up
